---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <!-- Hero Section with Beach Background -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1>Swallowing evaluations made easy.</h1>
      <p>
        Speech therapy options for adults. Services provided in your home, your doctor's office, 
        or our clinic locations in Port St. Lucie and Daytona Beach, FL.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:suzanne@smartimagingservices.net?subject=Patient%20Inquiry" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Specialty Section -->
  <section class="specialty section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our Specialty: F.E.E.S</h2>
      <p class="specialty-subtitle">FEES: Fiberoptic Endoscopic Evaluation of Swallowing</p>
      <div class="specialty-content">
        <p>
          FEES is one of two methods used to visualize the swallow in action. FEES is unique in that it allows clinicians 
          to bring the evaluation to the patient (portable). This means no more expensive hospital trips and obtaining the 
          results of the assessment is immediate.
        </p>
        <p class="highlight-text">
          If you or a loved one suspect you may have difficulty swallowing or frequent pneumonias then you may be a candidate for FEES.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How is it done Section -->
  <section class="info-section section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-row">
        <div class="info-image">
          <img src="/images/image-scoping.png" alt="Beach boardwalk representing Florida locations" />
        </div>
        <div class="info-content">
          <h2>How is it done?</h2>
          <p>
            FEES utilizes a small camera/scope to view the pharynx (throat) while the patient is eating. 
            The assessment is extremely fast with minimal discomfort.
          </p>
          <p>
            This assessment is for anyone experiencing signs of dysphagia or in an at risk population such as: 
            neurological disorders, stroke victims, traumatic brain injuries, gastric diseases, oropharyngeal cancers, etc.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What can FEES do Section -->
  <section class="info-section section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-row reverse">
        <div class="info-content">
          <h2>What can FEES do for me?</h2>
          <p>
            FEES allows your therapist to directly view how your muscles and nerves work together to efficiently 
            propel food as well as safely protect your airway. After FEES, your therapist can formulate a plan of 
            care to target your specific needs.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you have already been evaluated by an SLP and placed on a restricted/modified diet or utilize a 
            feeding tube then you may be a candidate for re-evaluation. Recommendations for modified diets or 
            feeding tubes without first obtaining a FEES or MBSS have been proven to be frequently inaccurate 
            and is not considered evidenced-based practice.
          </p>
          <p>
            Due to quickly advancing medical science, it may be difficult to find a therapist who is competent in 
            reading/interpreting FEES or MBSS. We are here to help you find the right fit for you and will connect 
            you with an experienced therapist in your area if our locations are inaccessible to you.
          </p>
          <p class="resource-note">
            *Please review our resource tab to find current ethics issues regarding swallowing diagnostics and therapies.*
          </p>
          <a href="/about-fees" class="btn btn-outline">Learn More</a>
        </div>
        <div class="info-image">
          <img src="/images/pexels-josh-willink-2701598-scaled.jpg" alt="Caring for patients" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ASHA Section -->
  <section class="asha-section section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="asha-content">
        <div class="asha-logo">
          <img src="/images/Screen-Shot-2019-03-04-at-2.05.07-PM-1.png" alt="ASHA - American Speech-Language-Hearing Association" />
        </div>
        <div class="asha-text">
          <h3>What ASHA says about bringing FEES to your facility:</h3>
          <time datetime="2021-07-12">July 12, 2021</time>
          <a href="https://leader.pubs.asha.org/doi/full/10.1044/leader.OTP.24032019.38" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="asha-link">
            https://leader.pubs.asha.org/doi/full/10.1044/leader.OTP.24032019.38
          </a>
          <p class="asha-title">Build a Case For Instrumental Swallowing Assessments in Long-Term Care</p>
          <p>Armed with facts and evidence, SLPs can help change policies that deny instrumental swallowing</p>
          <a href="https://leader.pubs.asha.org/doi/full/10.1044/leader.OTP.24032019.38" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline">
            See More
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero Section with Beach Background */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 550px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: url('/images/AdobeStock_299372852-scaled.jpeg') center/cover no-repeat;
    margin: 0 2rem;
  }

  .hero-content {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) var(--spacing-md);
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .hero p {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* Section Base */
  .section {
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  /* Specialty Section */
  .specialty {
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .specialty h2 {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .specialty-subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-decoration: underline;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .specialty-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .specialty-content p {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .highlight-text {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  /* Info Sections */
  .info-section {
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .info-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .info-row.reverse {
    direction: rtl;
  }

  .info-row.reverse > * {
    direction: ltr;
  }

  .info-image {
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .info-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .info-content h2 {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .info-content p {
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .resource-note {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  /* ASHA Section */
  .asha-section {
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .asha-content {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    align-items: flex-start;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .asha-logo {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 180px;
  }

  .asha-logo img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .asha-text h3 {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .asha-text time {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .asha-link {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    word-break: break-all;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .asha-title {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .asha-text > p:last-of-type {
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero {
      margin: 0 1rem;
      min-height: 400px;
    }

    .info-row,
    .info-row.reverse {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      direction: ltr;
    }

    .info-image {
      order: -1;
    }

    .asha-content {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .asha-logo {
      width: 150px;
    }
  }
</style>
